HEADWORD: Sagittocyst
<hw>Sag"it*to*cyst</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sagitta</er>, and <er>Cyst</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
defensive cell containing a minute rodlike structure which may be
expelled. Such cells are found in certain Turbellaria.</def>⟦br⟧
